    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-15T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-15T20:00:00-05:00" n="629"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4767: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-16T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 16, 1932—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 16—12:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My March 15, 10 a.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>British Minister last evening forwarded to me the following text <pb
                            facs="0691" n="587" xml:id="pg_587"/> which had been given to him by the
                        Japanese Minister as a substitute for paragraph (3) of the original draft:
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“(3) A joint commission with neutral members to certify the carrying
                                out of the agreement under paragraphs (1) and (2) and to watch and
                                observe the general conditions in the evacuated area until a later
                                settlement.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Please note carefully additional wording which seems to indicate Japanese
                        desire that neutral commission police the evacuated area pending further
                        settlement. Does the Department desire that I permit our agents to
                        participate to this extent?</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>I perceive in this an intention to raise question of policing this area at
                        further conference.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
